casebody.data:
The ELMER COMPANY, Limited, etc., v. GUARANTY LIQUIDATING CORP. No. 8344. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 12, 1936. Geo. W. Fenimore, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, DENMAN, and MATHEWS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of motion of appellee, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal in above cause dismissed for failure of appellants to file record and docket cause, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
